
[1]labadist

   LAB'ADIST, n. the Labadists were followers of Jean de Labadie, who
   lived in the 17th century. They held that God can and does deceive men,
   that the observance of the sabbath is a matter of indifference, and
   other peculiar or heretical opinions.
